\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Printing the 8 bands of different colors involves using a 
\family typewriter
colors[]
\family default
 array (colors are 6-digit hexadecimal,
 interpreted RGB from left to right in their respective [0,255] range).
 We can then invoke the width and height of the OLED to evenly partition 8 bands,
 and draw the lines at each partition,
 assigning a different color to each.
 
\family typewriter
drawFastHLine()
\family default
 works for each horizontal line in an iterative loop,
 and 
\family typewriter
drawFastVLine()
\family default
is good for the vertical lines.
 We increment the respective axis for each by gaps of 
\family typewriter
SSD1351HEIGH / num_band
\family default
,
 and hold the other constant,
 achieving the intended functionality.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
In between each drawing,
 we call 
\family typewriter
UtilsDelay(DRAW_DELAY)
\family default
followed by 
\family typewriter
fillScreen(WHITE)
\family default
,
 which allows for an approximate 1.5 second interval in between each drawing,
 and the screen to refresh to white in preparation for the next one (otherwise all of these drawings will overlap!).
 The remaining checkoff drawings are drawn;
 these are pretty self-explanatory,
 since they are already implemented for us.
 Checkoff 1 is complete!
\end_layout

