\begin_layout Standard
We experienced several difficulties with this lab (hence why it was submitted one lab period late).
 I will break down the most notable ones,
 and try to offer an accounting of our Lab 2 experience.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
CCS project issues:
 Both of us experienced issues with building CCS projects correctly.
 Our linked resources were consistently broken and we were having trouble porting the progress from previous lab parts to current parts.
 It turns out,
 we were approaching the CCS project environment wrong:
 moving files outside of the operations of the CCS environment was not respecting changes to the path environment variables.
 Once we started manipulating the files in the CCS IDE,
 these problems were smoothed over.
 We also attempted to create several workspaces,
 but the organizational hierarchy of our folders left something to be desired,
 and it consistently confused the IDE.
 Once we opted for one workspace,
 with all projects at the root folder,
 these problems also disappeared.
 Our attempts to be organized and respect good GitHub etiquette culminated into these issues.
 Once we played nice with Texas Instruments software,
 there weren't any other significant issues here.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Hardware issues:
 A couple of times,
 we did not provision the right equipment for at-home work (mainly the connector pins).
 This ended up causing us to be late as well.
 We've configured out environment to ensure this does not happen again.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
SPI API subtleties:
 This was a serious bottleneck.
 The SPI API for speaking with Adafruit is rather confusing.
 Specifically,
 it has an internal Chip Select (discussed earlier in the report) at Pin 50,
 which conflicts with our manually set OLEDCS chip select at general-purpose Pin 02.
 Not enabling the internal CS,
 despite not really using it,
 caused us a lot of grief;
 our SPI functions were consistently stalling without doing this.
 Once we included it in the SPI configuration function,
 these problems disappeared,
 but it took longer than we'd care to admit to track the source of this issue.
 There were other SPI subtleties that ate up time,
 but this was the main one.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Dependency subtleties:
 There were some dependencies that we had trouble working with.
 Demos like those provided for I2C and SPI have a lot of code to make it work,
 and if you choose to leverage that code for your own CCS project and aren't careful,
 it is easy to miss a couple lines (if you are trying to input the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

glue code
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 manually).
 We were missing an I2C initialization in 
\family typewriter
main.c
\family default
 for Checkoff 4 that had us scratching our heads for awhile.
 In the future,
 we'll definitely be more observant when it comes to transporting dependency code.
\end_layout

